A parliamentary committee in Uganda
cleared three ministers, including the prime minister, of
corruption in oil deals after failing to get evidence against
them, Sunday Vision reported, citing the committeeâ€™s draft
report.  Prime Minister Amama Mbabazi, Foreign Affairs Minister Sam
Kutesa and Internal Affairs Hilary Onek were cleared of the
allegations, the Kampala-based newspaper reported. The report
will be released at the end of month, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
